commitResults.messageBody: Implement a skeletal version of Duke that starts by greeting the user, simply echos commands entered by the user, and exits when the user types bye.
Add the ability to store whatever text entered by the user and display them back to the user when requested.
Add the ability to mark tasks as done.

Add support for tracking three types of tasks:
1. ToDos: tasks without any date/time attached to it e.g., visit new theme park
2. Deadlines: tasks that need to be done before a specific date/time e.g., submit report by 11/10/2019 5pm
3. Events: tasks that start at a specific time and ends at a specific time e.g., team project meeting on 2/10/2019 2-4pm
Use the input/output redirection technique to semi-automate the testing of Duke.
Teach Duke to deal with errors such as incorrect inputs entered by the user.
Add support for deleting tasks from the list.
Fixed EXPECTED.TXT and minor whitespace changes in Duke.java

Level 7. Save
Save the tasks in the hard disk automatically whenever the task list changes. Load the data from the hard disk when Duke starts up. You may hard-code the file name and location e.g., [project_root]/data/duke.txt

Level 8. Dates and Times
Teach Duke how to understand dates and times. For example, if the command is deadline return book /by 2/12/2019 1800, Duke should understand 2/12/2019 1800 as 2nd of December 2019, 6pm, instead of treating it as just a String.
Refactor the code to extract out closely related code as classes.
Organize the classes into suitable java packages.
Add JUnit tests to test the behavior of the code

commitResults.messageTitle: Tweak code to comply with Java coding standards

commitResults.messageBody:
Add assertions to various points in the code

There are several assumptions that should hold at various points in the
code. These assumptions are critical for the program to run smoothly.

Adding assertions can detect possible bugs in the code because when an
assertion error is thrown, it indicates that the code has violated an
assumption about how the code should behave.

This commit also contains a bug fix for when the program loads a task
that was marked done from the save file, the task is added into the
list without being marked done.

Update DukeList

Updated DukeList to comply with checkstyle standards.

Refactor Code

Command classes (e.g DeadlineCommand, DeleteCommand, DoneCommand)
and the DialogBox class have some code fragment that can be grouped
together.

Those fragments can be extracted and turned into a method whose name
explains the purpose of the method.

Extracting the code fragments can improve the program's internal
structure, improving the code quality and making it easier for future
developers to read, understand and modify the code.

Let's extract the code fragments that can be grouped together into
another method, stringifyMessage for Command classes, initialiseLoader
and setDisplay for DialogBox.

Add help command

There are currently no commands to help users with the program.

Adding a help command can help new users learn about the many commands
available and their usage.

Let's add a help command that when triggered, display a list of
available commands and their usage.
